  "texts": [
    "The focus of this study is on utilizing semantic knowledge extracted from oncology along with item-based CF, thus a review of related research studies has been conducted within this scope.Ontology has demonstrated its effectiveness in addressing certain limitations of collaborative filtering algorithms.",
    "Its implementation has shown promising results in improving recommendation system accuracy and alleviating the challenges posed by new item cold-start problems and sparsity.To improve the accuracy and reliability of collaborative filtering recommendations within e-commerce, Martín-Vicente et al. [17] presented a new strategy based on an ontology, which encapsulates the semantic representation of commercial goods.",
    "The exploitation of semantics enables reasoning about the data stored in the users' profiles and inferring new knowledge.",
    "Such new knowledge enhances recommendations in two ways: by refining neighborhood selection based on candidate trustworthiness and by adjusting the prediction process to value contributions from more experienced users.Martín-Vicente, et al. [52] introduced an improved hybrid approach for recommending products in the e-commerce domain.",
    "Their hybrid approach mainly avoids selecting fake neighborhoods in collaborative filtering recommender systems with diverse products."
